# Testing Rules

## MUST
- Follow the active version acceptance criteria.
- Follow `docs/rules/agent-verification-workflow.md`: fix → verify → report; never hand off unverified fixes to the user.
- Test critical business logic.
- Test auth and admin permissions.
- Test API validation and error cases.
- Add UI smoke tests for new key pages required by the active version.
- Run lint, typecheck, and relevant tests before marking work complete when available.
- For API/Admin/Web integration changes: curl or browser-check the affected routes before saying done.

## REQUIRED BACKEND TESTS
- Service unit tests.
- Guard tests.
- API integration tests.
- Job handler tests.
- Provider mock tests.

## REQUIRED FRONTEND TESTS
- Add smoke tests when introducing key pages such as Home, Feed Detail, AI Search, Watchlist, Admin Dashboard, and Admin Feed.

## FORBIDDEN
- Do not remove tests to pass.
- Do not disable lint or typecheck.
- Do not mark acceptance complete without verification.

## FINAL REPORT
- Include tests run, tests passed, tests not run and why, and remaining risk.
